# Trivy ignore file — CVEs we've reviewed and accepted.
#
# Every entry MUST have:
#   1. The CVE ID.
#   2. A comment linking to a decision entry in docs/security/DEPENDENCY_DECISIONS.md
#      OR docs/security/SECURITY_DECISIONS.md.
#   3. The date of acceptance.
#
# Reconsider each acceptance at the quarterly security review.
# If a CVE gets a fix, remove it from this file so the scan fails until the
# fixed version is adopted.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Accepted CVEs
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Base-image Debian OS CVEs — tracked in DEPENDENCY_DECISIONS.md
# 2026-07-04 acceptance.
# These are fixed in newer Debian package versions and will drop off
# automatically when the node:20-slim base image rebuilds against a
# fresher Debian snapshot. Reconsider quarterly per SOC 2 review.
CVE-2026-4878   # libcap2: TOCTOU privesc (base image)
CVE-2026-33845  # libgnutls30: DTLS zero-length DoS (base image)
CVE-2026-33846  # libgnutls30: heap buffer overflow DoS (base image)
CVE-2026-42009  # libgnutls30: DTLS reordering DoS (base image)
CVE-2026-42010  # libgnutls30: NUL character auth bypass (base image)
CVE-2026-3833   # libgnutls30: policy bypass, case sensitivity (base image)

# Python package CVEs in server/pyextract dependencies —
# reconsider at next PDF pipeline refresh, target Q3 2026.
CVE-2025-64512  # pdfminer.six < 20251107
CVE-2025-70559  # pdfminer.six < 20251230
CVE-2026-25990  # pillow < 12.1.1: OOB write via crafted image
CVE-2026-40192  # pillow < 12.2.0: decompression-bomb DoS
CVE-2026-42311  # pillow < 12.2.0: additional; same acceptance batch

# Dockerfile misconfig — client/Dockerfile.prod runs the nginx master as
# root to bind port 80. Standard nginx image behavior. Nginx worker processes
# drop privileges to the `nginx` user automatically. Container is deployed
# behind Cloudflare + host nginx, so port 80 in-container is not
# customer-facing. Reconsider at post-demo hardening: switch to
# nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged:1.25-alpine (binds to 8080, runs as UID 101)
# and update docker-compose port mapping accordingly.
DS-0002  # nginx-master-as-root — client/Dockerfile.prod
